          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION, Bordeaux France<BR><BR><BR>Bilingual English & German<BR><BR><BR>You will be based in Bordeaux and responsible for IN-FUSIO's German, UK, BeNeLux and Nordic  countries project management. You will have the responsibility of planning, coordinating, setting up and guaranteeing the smooth running of the Game Channel Management services (e.g. SMS-C/Customer care/Data access/Billing links) with VodafoneD2, Orange UK, Orange NL, etc…<BR><BR><BR>PRINCIPLE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES <BR><BR>·	You will be responsible for the successful completion of the project by setting the project plans and managing the Game Centre launch and follow-up for our clients (operators)<BR>·	You will act as the coordinator between the R&D, Marketing, Game Development, Test & Validation and Operations teams<BR>·	You will also be the main  interface with our clients and take care of customer customisation in coordination with the Area Sales Manager.<BR>·	You will guarantee the optimal functioning of all products/services launched by testing daily<BR>·	You will work in close collaboration with our Area Sales Manager in the preparation of project proposals to clients<BR>·	You will participate in the preparation of project plans or feasibility studies for new projects<BR><BR><BR>EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS REQUIRED<BR><BR>·	You are extremely comfortable dealing with technical issues (ideally a qualified Software Engineer or equivalent)<BR>·	You have at least 2 years experience in technical/telecommunications project management (knowledge of the German/UK  operators would be a real plus)<BR>·	You have a sound basis in the area of sales and client relationships<BR>·	You speak fluent English and German <BR>·	You are committed, organised and rigorous in your work with room for fun<BR>·	You have excellent listening and negotiation skills<BR>·	You must be successful at managing change and at ease in a fast moving-environment<BR><BR>If you are a flexible, proactive individual and you are eager to be a member of a very international sales team (Dutch, Spanish, Italian, French, Iranian, Chinese…) and contribute to the further growth of this highly international company (English is the working language), then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.  Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR>
<B></B><BR>
